<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Zend Tool could easily integrate with PHPUnit for Project based testing. Currently zf create project creates some testing related resources, but they are not used.</p>

<ol><li>Remove application/ and library/ distinction they dont pair with how PHPUnit works</li>
<li>Add a folder tests in each module, i.e. "modules/blog/tests", "modules/guestbook/tests".</li>
<li>Add two phpunit.xml one called unittest.xml, one functional.xml in the APP_ROOT/tests/ mainfolder, they both configure bootstrapFile="" a specific unit-test bootstrap file.</li>
<li>Add a AllFunctionalTests TestSuite in APP_ROOT/tests which detects all tests in folders and subfolders of all module tests/ folders (functionality is in phpunit already via Glob or something.)</li>
<li>Add a AllTests File which includes the AllFunctionalTests</li>
<li>Add a Bootstrap File that somehow gathers all autoloader specific resources (is that possible Matthew?!)</li>
</ol><p>Big advantages:
* Functional tests reside in the module they belong too, yet they are aggregated by a specific TestSuite mechanism.
* We use PHPUnit functionality to gather the unittests, so we don't need to rely on our own additional mechanism (KISS!)</p>

<p>The following commands are now available:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
zf run test
zf run test.(functional|unit) 
zf create test.functional </code></pre>

